tmux ------> new alternative for screen

below are the commands

#########

tmux  ----> create new session
tmux a    ---> attach session
tmux list-sesssions   -----> list session that are running
tmux a -t 0 ---->    tmux attach the session
ctrl b d --> to detach the session
ctrl b % ----> split the windows in multiple tabs
ctrl b q ----> to display the split windows number
ctrl b q 1 -----> give number to jump to that session
Resize Panes in tmux :
Press Ctrl + b, then press : to bring up the command prompt.

Resize down: resize-pane -D (for moving the border down)

Resize up: resize-pane -U (for moving the border up)

Resize left: resize-pane -L (for moving the border left)

Resize right: resize-pane -R (for moving the border right)


screen ----> in old linux

screen ----> create new session
screen -r ----> reattach session
screen -ls  ----> List all running screen sessions:
screen -r session-name ----> to reattach that session
ctrl + a, then d   ---> to detattach the session






vim/vi editor


0 - jump to the start of the line

$ - jump to the end of the line

gg - go to the first line of the document
G - go to the last line of the document

} - jump to next paragraph (or function/block, when editing code)
{ - jump to previous paragraph (or function/block, when editing code)

e press in the linux to go to next character
b press in the linux to go to end character

dd to deleting
:%d delete all things
dG will delete all lines from where you stand
yy copy
p paste


to copy in Visual press v then select the lines you want to copy
after that then
press y to copy and then p for paste


copy and replace in vim

:%s/word/new-word/g

add multiple comment in vim


:[start line],[end line]s/^/#

how to uncomment multiple lines

:%s/^#/


/word   search from top of file

?word    search from bottom of the file

gg go to top of the file

G go to end of the file

w go to word by word

b go to backword word by word

dd to delete lines

yy to copy 

3yy yo copy 3 lines



vim +8092 catalina.out    open the file from specified line

:linenumber              go to that line

:set number

:set nonumber

:set ignorecase


search for whole word with space
/\<your_exact_word\>

Visual mode 

use v and y for copy


:%s/old/new/g - replace all old with new throughout file
:%s/old/new/gc - replace all old with new throughout file with confirmations
:noh[lsearch] - remove highlighting of search
search for whole word with space
/\<your_exact_word\>






